Umbilo SAPS are investigating a case of attempted murder after a 54-year old man was shot several times in Dalton Mens Hostel, in Umbilo, last Friday night.Lieutenant Pumzile Makaula of the Umbilo SAPS explained that Constable L Dlamini was conducting a routine patrol of the area when he noticed a group of people gathering at the main gate of Dalton Mens Hostel. He was informed by residents that a man had been shot and was being transported to King Edward Hospital. Although Dlamini followed the vehicle to the hospital, he was unable to speak to the victim, who had sustained multiple gunshot wounds to the hand, stomach, thigh and cheek and was unable to speak. A case of attempted murder was opened and police are investigating the incident further.